remarks: Strong extensionality of multiplication (expressed in terms of ` <RR ` ).  Axiom for real and complex numbers, derived from set theory.  This construction-dependent theorem should not be referenced directly; instead, use ~ ax-pre-mulext . (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 18-Feb-2020.) (New usage is discouraged.)
statement: axpre-mulext $p |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( ( A x. C ) <RR ( B x. C ) -> ( A <RR B \/ B <RR A ) ) ) $.
